[00:00.00] In the central portion of the great North American Continent there lies an arid and repulsive desert, which for many a long year served as a barrier against the advance of civilisation.  From the Sierra Nevada（内华达州） to Nebraska（内布拉斯加州）, and from the Yellowstone River（黄石河） in the north to the Colorado（科罗拉多州） upon the south, is a region of desolation and silence. 
