[03:17.32]Here and there there are scattered white objects which glisten in the sun, and stand out against the dull deposit of alkali. Approach, and examine them! They are bones: some large and coarse, others smaller and more delicate. The former have belonged to oxen（牛）, and the latter to men. For fifteen hundred miles one may trace this ghastly（可怕的） caravan route by these scattered remains of those who had fallen by the wayside. 
